    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-09T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1744</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>
                        </placeName>, <lb/> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1917-02-09T11:30:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1917-02-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">Undated</hi>
                        </date>. <hi rend="italic">Received February 9, 1917, 11.30
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of February 5, 5 p.m. Upon renewed inquiry I find that the action
                    of Japanese Minister and banker was as reported in my January 15, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
